for the first time for five-atomic molecules. In the Supplementary Material we provide
the lists of theoretical intensities at 269 K for over 5000 strongest transitions
in the range below 6166 cmÃ¢Ë†â€™1. The advantage of the described method is that
this offers a possibility to generate fully assigned exhaustive line lists at various
temperature conditions. Extensive calculations up to 12000 cmÃ¢Ë†â€™1 including
high-T predictions will be made freely available through the TheoReTS information
system (http://theorets.univ-reims.fr, http://theorets.tsu.ru) that contains ab initio
